sections.title: How the population has changed in Flintshire
sections.label: Select another area to see how the population has changed

sections.content: In 2020, Flintshire was the sixth largest local authority in Wales, with a total population of 156,847. An increase compared with 2019.

sections.title: Population density in Flintshire
sections.content: In 2020, the population density in Flintshire was 357 people per square kilometre, which was more than Wales (153), and more than the United Kingdom as a whole (276).

sections.title: Median age in Flintshire
sections.content: In 2020, the median age in Flintshire was 44 years, which was older than Wales (42 years), and older than the United Kingdom as a whole (41 years).
